{{about|the 21st century executive|the early 19th century industrialist|Éleuthère Irénée du Pont}}
'''Eleuthère ("Thère") I. du Pont''' is an American business executive. He has been a director of [[DuPont]] since 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dupont.com/corporate-functions/our-company/leadership/board-of-directors/articles/du-pont.html |title=Bio Eleuthere I. du Pont, President, Longwood Foundation &#124; DuPont USA |first= |last= |work=dupont.com |year=March 2015 |accessdate=May 8, 2015}}</ref> As of 2015, he is the former president of [[Wawa, Inc.|Wawa]], a convenience-grocery store franchise; and president of the [[Longwood Gardens|Longwood Foundation]], which supports cultural and related activities in Delaware.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.longwoodfoundation.com/ |title=Longwood Foundation Home Page |first= |last=|work=longwoodfoundation.com |year=2015 |accessdate=May 8, 2015}}</ref> He was formerly a senior vice president and CFO of [[drugstore.com]]. 

He is the son of former [[Governor of Delaware]] [[Pierre S. du Pont IV|Pete du Pont]] and a descendant of the French immigrant [[DuPont family]] that founded the DuPont corporation near Wilmington, Delaware in the early nineteenth century.

