'''Erik Engebretsen''' is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] businessperson.

He grew up as a baker's son in [[Grønland, Oslo]], but the family moved to [[Bestum]] in his youth. He took economics education at the [[BI Norwegian Business School]] and also studied at the [[University of Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Profilen: Fra chip til skip|work=Aftenposten Aften|date=5 February 1993|author=Width, Henrik|page=23|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He worked in Actinor, Unitor and Geco before he was hired as chief financial officer in [[Norsk Data]] in 1987. In 1989 he was promoted to chief executive officer of the crisis-stricken company.<ref>{{cite news|title=Navn i nyhetene|work=Aftenposten|date=30 August 1989|author=Hellstrøm, Ulf P.|page=5|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In the summer of 1992 he left Norsk Data to take over as director of the lines Oslo–Kiel and Oslo–Hirtshals in [[Color Line (ferry operator)|Color Line]]. He was succeeded by [[Tor Alfheim]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ny sjef i ND|work=Aftenposten Aften|date=20 July 1992|author=Dahl, Flemming|page=2|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He also chaired [[Aker Hospital]] from 1992.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erik Engebretsen ny styreformann ved Aker sykehus|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=27 January 1992|language=Norwegian}}</ref> The entire board resigned in late 1993, protesting small budgets.<ref>{{cite news|title=Styret ved Aker sykehus går|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=3 November 1993|language=Norwegian}}</ref> 

In 1996 Engebretsen went from Color Line to the clothing chain [[Adelsten]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Linje-direktør i Color Line|work=Aftenposten|date=11 September 1996|author=|page=2|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In 1999 he left Adelsten for another company in crisis, [[Tandberg Television]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ny sjef i Adelsten|work=Dagens Næringsliv|date=10 April 1999|author=|page=5|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Strammer grepet|work=Dagens Næringsliv|date=1 February 2000|author=Bjørklund, Ingrid|page=34|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He later became deputy chairman of Tandberg Television's board and chief executive of [[Gezina]].

